description:
Looks like this way https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/blob/master/lib/gitlab/database/count/reltuples_count_strategy.rb#L74

@a_akgun @alinamihaila Perhaps the information in https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/210363#note_304089944 helps to decide on a better [threshold](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/blob/master/lib/gitlab/database/count/reltuples_count_strategy.rb#L75). I don't see a reason not to dial this up to a few hours. It may influence the quality of the estimate, but for usage data purposes it may just be fine to look at a statistic that is even a day old or so.

Thinking it may be an easy fix to get this working again (before we move it to batch counters - which is totally valid on its own, but perhaps more effort).

### Summary

When uploading a conan package with exports, the base conan files are uploaded but not conan_sources.tgz and conan_export.tgz

### Steps to reproduce (Assuming conan is installed)
1. Follow steps to enable conan gitlab repo `https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/user/packages/conan_repository/`
1. Clone https://github.com/Zinnion/conan-spdlog
2. Navigate to directory and run `conan create .` or any specific naming convention for package
3. Run `conan upload conan-spdlog/* --test-folder=None` (Note required to have valid conan user from gitlab)
4. Notice that conan_sources.tgz does not upload.

### Example Project

(If possible, please create an example project here on GitLab.com that exhibits the problematic behavior, and link to it here in the bug report)

(If you are using an older version of GitLab, this will also determine whether the bug is fixed in a more recent version)

### What is the current *bug* behavior?

Export files are not uploaded along with the conan_package.tgz

### What is the expected *correct* behavior?

There should be conan_export.tgz and conan_sources.tgz included.

### Relevant logs and/or screenshots

Trace of conan upload. Note that there is no REST API call to upload conan_sources.tgz.
